Patch the upstream dephier so equally-low outlets are processed in a
deterministic order. Without this, `std::sort` stability and
`unordered_map` iteration order leave the meta-depression tree
implementation-defined, which prevents bit-exact comparison against the
Julia port (the leaf depressions match, but parent/child assignments
and per-meta-dep aggregate fields can differ).

**Status:** REQUIRED before building the helper tools (or upstream's
own fsm.exe). There is no bundled/patched copy of the C++ in this repo;
you apply this to your own upstream clone. The Julia test suite itself
(`Pkg.test()`, "Option A") does NOT need this — it only matters when
regenerating oracle data ("Option B"). Do NOT push upstream.

Apply against the dephier submodule of an upstream clone checked out at
the pinned commit (parent Barnes2020-FillSpillMerge
`1c499ea475c09b9f4c5da74ee5cc995de169db63`, which pins dephier to
`411f7d4ad344d74447b47cf9eb85acd536a4d8a1`):

  cd <upstream-clone>/submodules/dephier
  git apply <FSM_Julia>/tools/patches/dephier-deterministic-outlets.patch

See the FSM_Julia root README.md, "Testing" -> Option B, for the full
clone + checkout + patch + build recipe and the rationale ("C++
patches" section).

diff --git a/include/dephier/dephier.hpp b/include/dephier/dephier.hpp
index 47bb95c..3a6f83f 100644
--- a/include/dephier/dephier.hpp
+++ b/include/dephier/dephier.hpp
@@ -617,8 +617,13 @@ DepressionHierarchy<elev_t> GetDepressionHierarchy(
   outlet_database = outletdb_t();

   //Sort outlets in order from lowest to highest. Takes O(N log N) time.
+  //Tie-break on (depa, depb, out_cell) so the order is fully deterministic
+  //regardless of `std::sort` stability and `unordered_map` iteration order.
+  //This makes the Julia port comparison robust; physically the algorithm is
+  //insensitive to which equally-low outlet is picked.
   std::sort(outlets.begin(), outlets.end(), [](const Outlet<elev_t> &a, const Outlet<elev_t> &b){
-    return a.out_elev<b.out_elev;
+    return std::tie(a.out_elev, a.depa, a.depb, a.out_cell)
+         < std::tie(b.out_elev, b.depa, b.depb, b.out_cell);
   });

